In this statement, the President of the United States congratulates the people of Zambia on their recent elections and commends their commitment to multiparty democracy. The President looks forward to working with President Michael Sata and other political leaders to strengthen the partnership between the United States and Zambia. The President also acknowledges the contributions of former President Rupiah Banda to Zambia's democratic development. He emphasizes that the hard work of a living democracy continues even after elections, and encourages Zambians to find common ground and address the challenges and opportunities facing their country.